ncalculable. I must say he&rsquo;s made significant progress with his three point shooting since he joined nets. Unfortunately his leg injury has progressed fairly rapidly over the past three weeks causing him to be sidelined for five months with a bad leg injury. His friend LeBron James will also be out of commission until his back heals. He hasn&rsquo;t made much progress with his shooting since he injured his back. His doctor 👨🏻&zwj;⚕️ said he was making good progress and will check on his progress next month. He assigned the blame for his back injury to a lack of stretching 🙆🏻&zwj;♂️ and training. Oh well 😔 it could be worse. His worth of contribution to Lakers is incalculable. Lakers is as likely to win the finals next year as Cavaliers in my opinion. The other month Lakers didn&rsquo;t just beat Bulls. They wiped the floor with them. The role of every coach in every team is well defined. In addition, the government has set up a commission to examine the use of steroids among NBA players. Another commission has been appointed to investigate family violence in NBA which I wholeheartedly support. Besides basketball, I&rsquo;m also a boxing fan. Floyd will be fighting in Las Vegas next February. If he tests positive for steroids again, the fans will be terribly disappointed with him. The promoter will also be bitterly disappointed in him as last year two of his tests came back positive. As a result he was suspended for half a year. However if he loses because of ring rust due to having been suspended for half a year, the fans including me will be deeply disappointed at the result. My brother who&rsquo;s a boxing fan too will be disappointed by the fact that he loses due to ring rust because of having been suspended. Last year I was a bit disappointed to find his fight with Ricky was overturned to a no contest because he failed the drug tests. The fans were disappointed too to hear he would be suspended."}]}